aa(lp330
VMore generally, I want to tell you something
p331
aVabout behavioral economics.
p332
aVWe have many intuitions in our life,
p333
aVand the point is that many of these intuitions are wrong.
p334
aVThe question is, are we going to test those intuitions?
p335
aVWe can think about how we're going to test this intuition
p336
aVin our private life, in our business life,
p337
aVand most particularly when it goes to policy,
p338
aVwhen we think about things like No Child Left Behind,
p339
aVwhen you create new stock markets, when you create other policies \u2014
p340
aVtaxation, health care and so on.
p341
aVAnd the difficulty of testing our intuition
p342
aVwas the big lesson I learned
p343
aVwhen I went back to the nurses to talk to them.
p344
aa(lp345
VSo I went back to talk to them
p346
aVand tell them what I found out about removing bandages.
p347
aVAnd I learned two interesting things.
p348
aVOne was that my favorite nurse, Ettie,
p349
aVtold me that I did not take her pain into consideration.
p350
aVShe said, "Of course, you know, it was very painful for you.
p351
aVBut think about me as a nurse,
p352
aVtaking, removing the bandages of somebody I liked,
p353
aVand had to do it repeatedly over a long period of time.
p354
aVCreating so much torture was not something that was good for me, too."
p355
aVAnd she said maybe part of the reason was it was difficult for her.
p356
aVBut it was actually more interesting than that, because she said,
p357
aV"I did not think that your intuition was right.
p358
aVI felt my intuition was correct."
p359
aVSo, if you think about all of your intuitions,
p360
aVit's very hard to believe that your intuition is wrong.
p361
aVAnd she said, "Given the fact that I thought my intuition was right ..." \u2014
p362
aVshe thought her intuition was right \u2014
p363
aVit was very difficult for her to accept doing a difficult experiment
p364
aVto try and check whether she was wrong.
p365
aa(lp366
VBut in fact, this is the situation we're all in all the time.
p367
aVWe have very strong intuitions about all kinds of things \u2014
p368
aVour own ability, how the economy works,
p369
aVhow we should pay school teachers.
p370
aVBut unless we start testing those intuitions,
p371
aVwe're not going to do better.
p372
aVAnd just think about how better my life would have been
p373
aVif these nurses would have been willing to check their intuition,
p374
aVand how everything would have been better
p375
aVif we just start doing more systematic experimentation of our intuitions.
p376
aa(lp377
VThank you very much.
